A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Denise Jordan; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Denise Jordan began her career with the City of Gainesville in July 1990 as an
3 entry-level employee within the Gainesville Police Department, and through her dedication
4 and excellence, she rose to become city clerk in February 2000; and
5 WHEREAS, during her exemplary tenure, she has played a crucial role in modernizing city
6 processes, transitioning from manual to electronic processing for agendas, agenda packets,
7 and campaign contribution disclosure reports as well as facilitating improvements for
8 audio/visual equipment and the podium in the Gainesville Municipal Courtroom; and
9 WHEREAS, she further coordinated efforts to recodify the Code of Ordinances and Unified
10 Land Development Code as well as led the transformation of the Historic Gainesville City
11 Hall basement into a dedicated archive space with guidance and assistance from the Georgia
12 Archives, preserving the city's historical records for future generations; and
13 WHEREAS, over the past 25 years, Denise Jordan has provided steadfast support to 13
14 council members and four city managers; and
