15 WHEREAS, she has long been an active and influential member of the Georgia Municipal
16 Clerks Association, serving in many roles before and after her tenure as president in
17 2009-2010, and she was honored as the association's 2015-2016 Clerk of the Year; and
18 WHEREAS, she is one of only 15 clerks in the State of Georgia to receive the Master
19 Municipal Clerk designation from the International Institute of Municipal Clerks, and she has
20 made history as the first clerk in the State of Georgia to become an Athenian Dialogue
21 Facilitator through the institute, joining an elite group of only nine facilitators in the region
22 and 93 across the United States and Canada; and
23 WHEREAS, upon her well-deserved retirement, she looks forward to spending more time
24 with family and friends, becoming more active in her church's youth department, remodeling
25 her home, taking cake-decorating classes, continuing her nonprofit volunteer work with
26 Bloom Enterprises, improving her gardening skills, and traveling; and
27 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
28 remarkable and distinguished Georgian be appropriately honored during this special time.
29 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
30 recognize and commend Denise Jordan for her efficient, effective, unselfish, and dedicated
31 service to the City of Gainesville; congratulate her upon the grand occasion of her retirement;
32 and extend the most sincere best wishes for continued health and happiness.
33 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
34 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Denise Jordan.
